      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (RH index) directly maps to the clinical hemolysis endpoint; secondary QoIs (shear stress, exposure time) support mechanistic interpretation.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the regulatory acceptance criterion for CPB device comparison against the predicate. Shear stress magnitude and exposure time are intermediate QoIs that feed the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model implemented in the post-processing module. These QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
