      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating conditions span the COU design space; fluid properties match clinical blood analog.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, the same geometry as the COU device. The porcine blood analog (40% hematocrit, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) is representative of clinical conditions. The five validation operating points bracket the worst-case hemolysis region identified in the parametric sweep."
    },
