      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison with higher-fidelity reference data or literature for rotating pump geometries.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on published benchmark studies for centrifugal blood pumps showing superior performance over k-ε variants in regions of adverse pressure gradient near the impeller trailing edge. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model is the accepted regulatory standard for this device class."
    },
    {
